me":"342f","__typename":"Paragraph","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"In our case, I added the note from https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fmmatloka\u002Fmachine-learning-by-example-workshop (ensure the link to the raw contents of the json file is used i.e. https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fmmatloka\u002Fmachine-learning-by-example-workshop\u002Fmaster\u002FWorkshop.json) into Zeppelin, and tried running but got various errors when trying to run the first couple of paragraphs.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_54.markups.0","typename":"Markup"},{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_54.markups.1","typename":"Markup"},{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_54.markups.2","typename":"Markup"}],"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_54.markups.0":{"type":"CODE","start":144,"end":148,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null,"__typename":"Markup"},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_54.markups.1":{"type":"A","start":35,"end":99,"href":"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Fmmatloka\u002Fmachine-learning-by-example-workshop","anchorType":"LINK","userId":null,"linkMetadata":null,"__typename":"Markup"},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_54.markups.2":{"type":"A","start":167,"end":267,"href":"https:\u002F\u002Fraw.githubusercontent.com\u002Fmmatloka\u002Fmachine-learning-by-example-workshop\u002Fmaster\u002FWorkshop.json","anchorType":"LINK","userId":null,"linkMetadata":null,"__typename":"Markup"},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_55":{"id":"52ed1a897d48_55","name":"b024","__typename":"Paragraph","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Looking for answers as to why I was getting those errors, I came across a forum and then took upon the suggestion from someone on the forum where similar errors messages were reported. It was a workaround to fix issue https:\u002F\u002Fissues.apache.org\u002Fjira\u002Fbrowse\u002FZEPPELIN-3586.","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_55.markups.0","typename":"Markup"}],"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_55.markups.0":{"type":"A","start":218,"end":269,"href":"https:\u002F\u002Fissues.apache.org\u002Fjira\u002Fbrowse\u002FZEPPELIN-3586","anchorType":"LINK","userId":null,"linkMetadata":null,"__typename":"Markup"},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_56":{"id":"52ed1a897d48_56","name":"1c24","__typename":"Paragraph","type":"H3","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"We failed the previous time, so let’s try again…","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[],"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_57":{"id":"52ed1a897d48_57","name":"dfe7","__typename":"Paragraph","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"One of the solutions was to make SPARK_HOME point to a separate instance of Spark and not rely on the embeddedspark interpreter inside the Apache Zeppelin installation. As a workaround, a link to a Dockerfile gist was provided at https:\u002F\u002Fgist.github.com\u002Fconker84\u002F4ffc9a2f0125c808b4dfcf3b7d70b043#file-zeppelin-dockerfile. I extended the script to incorporate GraalVM JRE and added the necessary configuration for it to be visible to Zeppelin and Spark:","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_57.markups.0","typename":"Markup"},{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_57.markups.1","typename":"Markup"},{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_57.markups.2","typename":"Markup"}],"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_57.markups.0":{"type":"CODE","start":33,"end":43,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null,"__typename":"Markup"},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_57.markups.1":{"type":"CODE","start":110,"end":127,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null,"__typename":"Markup"},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_57.markups.2":{"type":"A","start":230,"end":320,"href":"https:\u002F\u002Fgist.github.com\u002Fconker84\u002F4ffc9a2f0125c808b4dfcf3b7d70b043#file-zeppelin-dockerfile","anchorType":"LINK","userId":null,"linkMetadata":null,"__typename":"Markup"},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_58":{"id":"52ed1a897d48_58","name":"7080","__typename":"Paragraph","type":"P","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"Zeppelin-Dockerfile","hasDropCap":null,"dropCapImage":null,"markups":[{"type":"id","generated":true,"id":"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_58.markups.0","typename":"Markup"}],"iframe":null,"mixtapeMetadata":null},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_58.markups.0":{"type":"EM","start":0,"end":19,"href":null,"anchorType":null,"userId":null,"linkMetadata":null,"__typename":"Markup"},"Paragraph:52ed1a897d48_59":{"id":"52ed1a897d48_59","name":"21e4","__typename":"Paragraph","type":"PRE","href":null,"layout":null,"metadata":null,"text":"FROM apache\u002Fzeppelin:0.8.0\n# Workaround to &quot;fix&quot; https:\u002F\u002Fissues.apache.org\u002Fjira\u002Fbrowse\u002FZEPPELIN-3586\nRUN echo &quot;$LOG_TAG Download Spark binary&quot; && \\\nwget -O \u002Ftmp\u002Fspark-2.3.1-bin-hadoop2.7.tgz http:\u002F\u002Fapache.panu.it\u002Fspark\u002Fspark-2.3.1\u002Fspark-2.3.1-bin-hadoop2.7.tgz && \\\ntar -zxvf \u002Ftmp\u002Fspark-2.3.1-bin-hadoop2.7.tgz && \\\nrm -rf \u002Ftmp\u002Fspark-2.3.1-bin-hadoop2.7.tgz && \\\nmv spark-2.3.1-bin-hadoop2.7 \u002Fspark-2.3.1-bin-hadoop2.7\nENV SPARK_HOME=\u002Fspark-2.3.1-bin-hadoop2.7\n### My modified steps here on:\nRUN rm -fr \u002Fusr\u002Flib\u002Fjvm\u002Fjava-1.8.0-openjdk-amd64 \u002Fusr\u002Flib\u002Fjvm\u002Fjava-8-openjdk-amd64\nRUN wget https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Foracle\u002Fgraal\u002Freleases\u002Fdownload\u002Fvm-1.0.0-rc10\u002Fgraalvm-ce-1.0.0-rc10-linux-amd64.tar.gz\nRUN tar xvzf graalvm-ce-1.0.0-rc10-linux-amd64.tar.gz\nRUN mv graalvm-ce-1.0.0-rc10\u002Fjre \u002Fusr\u